                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2669: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 21, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>574. My telegram No. 565, of November 18, 9 p.m. President this afternoon
                    confirmed Minister of Finance’s statement to me that group loan would be settled
                    within the near future. However, he was apparently somewhat confused as he
                    mentioned obtaining the enabling legislation which the Minister does not believe
                    to be necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
